lifetime in the hit network

00:02:58.220 --> 00:03:00.900 align:middle line:10%
television show
"Touched by an Angel."

00:03:00.900 --> 00:03:03.140 align:middle line:10%
Her spirit and
determination have

00:03:03.140 --> 00:03:05.390 align:middle line:10%
inspired millions of people.

00:03:05.390 --> 00:03:12.710 align:middle line:84%
And she has proven that she
is truly an angel among us.

00:03:12.710 --> 00:03:16.600 align:middle line:84%
Della, thank you for
sitting down with us today.

00:03:16.600 --> 00:03:19.330 align:middle line:90%
I know God is in this room.

00:03:19.330 --> 00:03:21.100 align:middle line:84%
But since you do it
so well, will you

00:03:21.100 --> 00:03:24.730 align:middle line:84%
remind us all with a
blessing before we begin?

00:03:24.730 --> 00:03:26.620 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, you have
just blessed us.

00:03:26.620 --> 00:03:30.590 align:middle line:10%
You've recognized that
God is in the midst of us.

00:03:30.590 --> 00:03:33.760 align:middle line:84%
And the thing that
I think makes people

00:03:33.760 --> 00:03:38.770 align:middle line:84%
so wary of having a relationship
with God-- there seems to be so

00:03:38.770 --> 00:03:41.630 align:middle line:90%
many forms you have to follow.

00:03:41.630 --> 00:03:43.990 align:middle line:90%
And it's not really necessary.

00:03:43.990 --> 00:03:47.920 align:middle line:84%
What's necessary is to know
that God lives inside you.

00:03:47.920 --> 00:03:51.410 align:middle line:84%
And you are in contact
with him whenever you

00:03:51.410 --> 00:03:53.830 align:middle line:90%
are consciously aware of him.

00:03:53.830 --> 00:03:59.140 align:middle line:84%
And since he does live inside
of you, you have all that He is.

00:03:59.140 --> 00:04:01.240 align:middle line:90%
And He is a blessing power.

00:04:01.240 --> 00:04:03.260 align:middle line:90%
So you just blessed all of us.

00:04:03.260 --> 00:04:04.060 align:middle line:90%
>> Wonderful.

00:04:04.060 --> 00:04:09.430 align:middle line:10%
Do you think, Della, that there
is a difference between prayer

00:04:09.430 --> 00:04:11.590 align:middle line:10%
and talking to God?

00:04:11.590 --> 00:04:13.050 align:middle line:90%
>> I don't.

00:04:13.050 --> 00:04:13.850 align:middle line:90%
I don't.

00:04:13.850 --> 00:04:16.339 align:middle line:90%
Every thought is a prayer.

00:04:16.339 --> 00:04:18.810 align:middle line:84%
I don't think you have
to come with flowery--

00:04:18.810 --> 00:04:22.630 align:middle line:84%
"Oh, Great Savior,
or Rose of Sharon,

00:04:22.630 --> 00:04:24.430 align:middle line:90%
oh bright and Morning Sun.

00:04:24.430 --> 00:04:25.540 align:middle line:90%
He's inside of me.

00:04:25.540 --> 00:04:28.240 align:middle line:84%
He knows I'm going
through a crisis right now

00:04:28.240 --> 00:04:31.330 align:middle line:84%
and I don't feel
Rose of Sharon-ish.

00:04:31.330 --> 00:04:35.560 align:middle line:84%
I feel I want to talk to God
who's my friend about what's

00:04:35.560 --> 00:04:36.710 align:middle line:90%
happening to me.

00:04:36.710 --> 00:04:38.840 align:middle line:90%
I got this from my mother.

00:04:38.840 --> 00:04:43.210 align:middle line:84%
She had a constant
conversation with God,

00:04:43.210 --> 00:04:47.080 align:middle line:84%
which taught me that nothing
is too small or too large.

00:04:47.080 --> 00:04:50.560 align:middle line:84%
Or there's nothing that
he is not aware of.

00:04:50.560 --> 00:04:53.500 align:middle line:84%
She would say, "Now,
Father, what are

00:04:53.500 --> 00:04:54.950 align:middle line:90%
we going to cook for dinner?

00:04:54.950 --> 00:04:55.750 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:04:55.750 --> 00:04:57.550 align:middle line:90%
And she'd listen.

00:04:57.550 --> 00:05:00.370 align:middle line:84%
And she'd say, "Oh
yeah, that'd be nice."

00:05:00.370 --> 00:05:04.660 align:middle line:84%
And so I as a child,
coming up I understood

00:05:04.660 --> 00:05:07.390 align:middle line:84%
a constant
relationship with God.

00:05:07.390 --> 00:05:09.880 align:middle line:90%
And I find it quite favorable.

00:05:09.880 --> 00:05:14.290 align:middle line:84%
>> It sounds to me that your
mother taught you and had great

00:05:14.290 --> 00:05:15.350 align:middle line:90%
faith.

00:05:15.350 --> 00:05:17.620 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, this is going to
sound kind of strange.

00:05:17.620 --> 00:05:19.260 align:middle line:90%
She didn't teach me.

00:05:19.260 --> 00:05:22.570 align:middle line:84%
She didn't say, "Now, this
is this and this is that."

00:05:22.570 --> 00:05:24.790 align:middle line:90%
She lived it every day.

00:05:24.790 --> 00:05:27.670 align:middle line:90%
It was a normal mean for her.

00:05:27.670 --> 00:05:29.670 align:middle line:90%
She and God laughed and talked.

00:05:29.670 --> 00:05:33.130 align:middle line:84%
And I don't know if I can
really explain it to you.

00:05:33.130 --> 00:05:37.340 align:middle line:84%
But as a child,
it didn't make Him

00:05:37.340 --> 00:05:41.980 align:middle line:84%
somewhere away that I
had to get in touch with.

00:05:41.980 --> 00:05:45.220 align:middle line:84%
It didn't make him
something I had to do.

00:05:45.220 --> 00:05:47.720 align:middle line:84%
Because He lived in
a house with my mama.

00:05:47.720 --> 00:05:48.520 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:05:48.520 --> 00:05:53.650 align:middle line:84%
So there was no thing I
had to be, or say, or do,

00:05:53.650 --> 00:05:56.230 align:middle line:90%
no form I had to fill out.

00:05:56.230 --> 00:05:57.430 align:middle line:90%
Because there He was.

00:05:57.430 --> 00:05:59.750 align:middle line:90%
He lived in the house with us.

00:05:59.750 --> 00:06:03.490 align:middle line:84%
And so my father
worked in a steel mill.

00:06:03.490 --> 00:06:05.920 align:middle line:84%
He poured steel,
literally poured steel.

00:06:05.920 --> 00:06:08.440 align:middle line:90%
And he made $65 a week.

00:06:08.440 --> 00:06:09.580 align:middle line:90%
And that was everything.

00:06:09.580 --> 00:06:11.470 align:middle line:84%
That was all the
money for everything.

00:06:11.470 --> 00:06:12.580 align:middle line:90%
And it would not last.

00:06:12.580 --> 00:06:14.380 align:middle line:90%
It would run out.

00:06:14.380 --> 00:06:15.250 align:middle line:90%
And she would sit--

00:06:15.250 --> 00:06:18.190 align:middle line:84%
we had this big ugly
green chair that she

00:06:18.190 --> 00:06:21.120 align:middle line:84%
would sit in with
her legs crossed,

00:06:21.120 --> 00:06:23.560 align:middle line:90%
in a yoga or Indian manner.

00:06:23.560 --> 00:06:26.170 align:middle line:90%
And she would moan and rock.

00:06:26.170 --> 00:06:27.490 align:middle line:90%
And she would talk to God.

00:06:27.490 --> 00:06:30.700 align:middle line:84%
And she would say,
"I've got enough meat

00:06:30.700 --> 00:06:32.170 align:middle line:90%
to make the lunches.

00:06:32.170 --> 00:06:34.900 align:middle line:84%
And I have some of
those black eyed peas

00:06:34.900 --> 00:06:36.490 align:middle line:90%
left from the other day.

00:06:36.490 --> 00:06:38.050 align:middle line:84%
And I've got a
couple of tomatoes.

00:06:38.050 --> 00:06:40.120 align:middle line:84%
And I could make
that for dinner.

00:06:40.120 --> 00:06:42.340 align:middle line:90%
But I don't have any bread.

00:06:42.340 --> 00:06:44.080 align:middle line:90%
And I really need some bread.

00:06:44.080 --> 00:06:47.045 align:middle line:84%
And the money has run-- but
you know the money's run out.

00:06:47.045 --> 00:06:47.920 align:middle line:90%
And there's no bread.

00:06:47.920 --> 00:06:49.360 align:middle line:90%
And I need some bread.

00:06:49.360 --> 00:06:53.650 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't that she was begging,
or asking, or anything.

00:06:53.650 --> 00:06:55.630 align:middle line:84%
It was very feasible
to me that he

00:06:55.630 --> 00:06:59.680 align:middle line:84%
was a constant presence,
ever available, always

00:06:59.680 --> 00:07:02.010 align:middle line:90%
interested in what you needed.

00:07:02.010 --> 00:07:07.300 align:middle line:84%
>> Then answer me this, if
you will is faith a gift?

00:07:07.300 --> 00:07:10.760 align:middle line:90%
>> All that God is, I am.

00:07:10.760 --> 00:07:15.320 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things
that He has given me

00:07:15.320 --> 00:07:20.000 align:middle line:84%
is his faith in me
to be as wonderful

00:07:20.000 --> 00:07:22.690 align:middle line:90%
as He created me to be.

00:07:22.690 --> 00:07:26.852 align:middle line:84%
So that's one of the
attributes that I have.

00:07:26.852 --> 00:07:29.130 align:middle line:84%
I'm made in his
image and likeness.

00:07:29.130 --> 00:07:33.300 align:middle line:84%
So if He has faith
in me, then faith

00:07:33.300 --> 00:07:37.740 align:middle line:84%
is one of the
faculties that is mine.

00:07:37.740 --> 00:07:40.830 align:middle line:84%
>> Della's faith was seriously
tested when she witnessed

00:07:40.830 --> 00:07:44.220 align:middle line:84%
the darker side of humanity
at the death of her very close

00:07:44.220 --> 00:07:47.280 align:middle line:90%
friend Redd Foxx.

00:07:47.280 --> 00:07:50.970 align:middle line:84%
>> I was on "Royal
Family" with Redd Foxx.

00:07:50.970 --> 00:07:55.470 align:middle line:84%
Redd Foxx fell in my arms
before he made his transition.

00:07:55.470 --> 00:08:00.180 align:middle line:84%
And I was so disgusted with
the way his wife was treated.

00:08:00.180 --> 00:08:03.240 align:middle line:84%
The doctor came out in
the hospital waiting room

00:08:03.240 --> 00:08:06.390 align:middle line:84%
and said to Mrs.
Foxx, "Your husband

00:08:06.390 --> 00:08:08.580 align:middle line:90%
has gone on, Mrs. Foxx."

00:08:08.580 --> 00:08:11.960 align:middle line:84%
And the powers that be for the
"Royal Family" said, "Well,

00:08:11.960 --> 00:08:13.440 align:middle line:90%
what are we going to do?

00:08:13.440 --> 00:08:15.726 align:middle line:84%
Because this script is
written for Redd and Della."

00:08:15.726 --> 00:08:17.350 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the woman is
sitting right here

00:08:17.350 --> 00:08:19.141 align:middle line:84%
and they were talking
like, "Well, maybe we

00:08:19.141 --> 00:08:21.720 align:middle line:84%
could get so-and-so and maybe
we could such and such."

00:08:21.720 --> 00:08:24.010 align:middle line:90%
Nobody has said, "Mrs. Foxx"--

00:08:24.010 --> 00:08:25.890 align:middle line:90%
now, I am livid.

00:08:25.890 --> 00:08:27.270 align:middle line:90%
It was so disrespectful.

00:08:27.270 --> 00:08:32.340 align:middle line:84%
I said I would not ever
do a situation comedy

00:08:32.340 --> 00:08:33.929 align:middle line:90%
or any kind of television show.

00:08:33.929 --> 00:08:37.530 align:middle line:84%
Because I wouldn't want them to
treat Franklin and my daughter,

00:08:37.530 --> 00:08:40.120 align:middle line:90%
Della Junior, that way.

00:08:40.120 --> 00:08:43.299 align:middle line:84%
>> Della's confidence in show
business was restored when she

00:08:43.299 --> 00:08:47.080 align:middle line:84%
was asked to start a new
television pilot about angels.

00:08:47.080 --> 00:08:50.860 align:middle line:84%
However, the show seemed to
have little chance of airing.

00:08:50.860 --> 00:08:53.890 align:middle line:84%
But with God on her
side, Della helped

00:08:53.890 --> 00:08:58.830 align:middle line:84%
make "Touched by an Angel"
a phenomenal success.

00:08:58.830 --> 00:09:00.950 align:middle line:90%
>> I get a call to come to CBS.

00:09:00.950 --> 00:09:02.420 align:middle line:90%
They want to talk to me.

00:09:02.420 --> 00:09:04.234 align:middle line:84%
And I go and they
tell me-- introduce me

00:09:04.234 --> 00:09:05.900 align:middle line:84%
to Martha Williamson
and tell me they're

00:09:05.900 --> 00:09:07.640 align:middle line:84%
going to do "Touched
by an Angel,"

00:09:07.640 --> 00:09:10.890 align:middle line:84%
but I'm not going to do
any more of this at all.

00:09:10.890 --> 00:09:13.076 align:middle line:84%
And I tell my husband,
who is my manager,

00:09:13.076 --> 00:09:14.450 align:middle line:84%
"Please tell them
in a nice way I

00:09:14.450 --> 00:09:16.620 align:middle line:84%
don't want to do this,
to get somebody else."

00:09:16.620 --> 00:09:18.810 align:middle line:84%
So he says, "Well,
think about it."

00:09:18.810 --> 00:09:22.880 align:middle line:84%
So I come home, and I went
in my room, got in my bed,

00:09:22.880 --> 00:09:23.859 align:middle line:90%
and prayed.

00:09:23.859 --> 00:09:25.400 align:middle line:84%
And I said, "Father,
you know I don't

00:09:25.400 --> 00:09:27.070 align:middle line:90%
like the corporate structure.

00:09:27.070 --> 00:09:29.070 align:middle line:84%
You know I don't like
working with these people.

00:09:29.070 --> 00:09:30.060 align:middle line:90%
They have no heart.

00:09:30.060 --> 00:09:31.470 align:middle line:90%
I'm very happy singing.

00:09:31.470 --> 00:09:32.270 align:middle line:90%
I'm comfortable.

00:09:32.270 --> 00:09:33.070 align:middle line:90%
You're blessing me.

00:09:33.070 --> 00:09:34.130 align:middle line:90%
And I'm fine."

00:09:34.130 --> 00:09:37.250 align:middle line:84%
And He said as clearly to
me as I'm saying to you,

00:09:37.250 --> 00:09:40.700 align:middle line:84%
"Do this for me and you
can retire in 10 years."

00:09:40.700 --> 00:09:43.160 align:middle line:90%
Very distinctly, He has English.

00:09:43.160 --> 00:09:46.310 align:middle line:84%
Very distinctly and
very big, you know?

00:09:46.310 --> 00:09:48.410 align:middle line:90%
And now, I've got to do this.

00:09:48.410 --> 00:09:50.969 align:middle line:84%
Because I can't disobey
him that boldly.

00:09:50.969 --> 00:09:52.760 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I sneak around
and do a few things.

00:09:52.760 --> 00:09:55.730 align:middle line:84%
But just boldly say, "No,
I'm not going to do that"--

00:09:55.730 --> 00:10:00.170 align:middle line:84%
so I start to do it, which I
find out later, my purpose,

00:10:00.170 --> 00:10:03.260 align:middle line:84%
not only to do the
show, but is to be there

00:10:03.260 --> 00:10:05.750 align:middle line:90%
because it's going to be rocky.

00:10:05.750 --> 00:10:07.700 align:middle line:84%
And because I'm
the one that knows

00:10:07.700 --> 00:10:10.470 align:middle line:84%
that it's going to be
successful for 10 years,

00:10:10.470 --> 00:10:14.690 align:middle line:84%
I'm supposed to be there to say
things, and do things, and hold

00:10:14.690 --> 00:10:16.370 align:middle line:90%
people together.

00:10:16.370 --> 00:10:18.500 align:middle line:84%
But it was funny,
because the first year

00:10:18.500 --> 00:10:21.170 align:middle line:84%
I said-- when it was over,
they gave us four shows,

00:10:21.170 --> 00:10:22.440 align:middle line:90%
they gave us six shows.

00:10:22.440 --> 00:10:23.990 align:middle line:90%
It took to get to 13--

00:10:23.990 --> 00:10:26.080 align:middle line:84%
so the 13th show,
they said, "That's it.

00:10:26.080 --> 00:10:27.307 align:middle line:90%
It's not going to work.

00:10:27.307 --> 00:10:28.640 align:middle line:90%
And we're not going to be back."

00:10:28.640 --> 00:10:30.140 align:middle line:10%
So I called everybody
together said,

00:10:30.140 --> 00:10:33.410 align:middle line:10%
"Take whatever you need kind
of job in order to survive,

00:10:33.410 --> 00:10:35.150 align:middle line:10%
because we're coming
back next year.

00:10:35.150 --> 00:10:38.130 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to be
the hit of the season.

00:10:38.130 --> 00:10:39.890 align:middle line:84%
So don't get hung
up in nothing so you

00:10:39.890 --> 00:10:42.270 align:middle line:84%
can't give back, because you
want to be a part of this."

00:10:42.270 --> 00:10:44.840 align:middle line:84%
So the second year,
they all came back

00:10:44.840 --> 00:10:47.367 align:middle line:84%
and we were the hit
of the season, OK?

00:10:47.367 --> 00:10:49.700 align:middle line:84%
Now, the first season when I
was telling them to hold on

00:10:49.700 --> 00:10:52.460 align:middle line:84%
and I was telling them God
said this, they're going,

00:10:52.460 --> 00:10:54.280 align:middle line:90%
"Uh huh, yeah, I know."

