about the love of her life,

00:14:01.510 --> 00:14:05.320 align:middle line:90%
her husband, Franklin Lett.

00:14:05.320 --> 00:14:11.860 align:middle line:84%
When you met Franklin, did you
walk slowly into love with him

00:14:11.860 --> 00:14:14.110 align:middle line:90%
or did you fall in love?

00:14:14.110 --> 00:14:15.610 align:middle line:90%
>> Neither, neither.

00:14:15.610 --> 00:14:18.900 align:middle line:84%
I went to apply for
a job with Franklin.

00:14:18.900 --> 00:14:21.950 align:middle line:84%
He was in marketing and
advertising at the time.

00:14:21.950 --> 00:14:26.170 align:middle line:84%
And he was looking for a
spokesperson for the Borden's

00:14:26.170 --> 00:14:28.802 align:middle line:84%
dairy product, the cross
over spokesman-- that

00:14:28.802 --> 00:14:31.260 align:middle line:84%
meant that the white people
liked you and the black people,

00:14:31.260 --> 00:14:31.460 align:middle line:90%
too.

00:14:31.460 --> 00:14:32.260 align:middle line:90%
>> Got it.

00:14:32.260 --> 00:14:34.120 align:middle line:84%
>> So I had been
recommended to him.

00:14:34.120 --> 00:14:36.170 align:middle line:84%
And for some reason,
he had turned me down.

00:14:36.170 --> 00:14:38.560 align:middle line:84%
He tried Carmen McRae,
and Nancy Wilson,

00:14:38.560 --> 00:14:41.260 align:middle line:84%
and several other people, but
he wasn't satisfied with them.

00:14:41.260 --> 00:14:44.410 align:middle line:84%
And Franklin said, OK, he
would take a meeting with me.

00:14:44.410 --> 00:14:45.670 align:middle line:90%
And we had the meeting.

00:14:45.670 --> 00:14:47.230 align:middle line:90%
It was a business meeting.

00:14:47.230 --> 00:14:48.280 align:middle line:90%
He was very nice.

00:14:48.280 --> 00:14:49.966 align:middle line:90%
He was not my type at all.

00:14:49.966 --> 00:14:50.840 align:middle line:90%
"Thank you very much.

00:14:50.840 --> 00:14:53.131 align:middle line:84%
Goodbye, call me when you've
got something to tell me."

00:14:53.131 --> 00:14:54.100 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:14:54.100 --> 00:14:55.450 align:middle line:90%
That's-- he did--

00:14:55.450 --> 00:14:57.340 align:middle line:90%
he was not my picture.

00:14:57.340 --> 00:14:58.260 align:middle line:90%
>> Stop it.

00:14:58.260 --> 00:14:59.095 align:middle line:90%
>> I'm serious.

00:14:59.095 --> 00:15:00.175 align:middle line:90%
>> He is so cute.

00:15:00.175 --> 00:15:01.615 align:middle line:90%
>> He Was not my picture.

00:15:01.615 --> 00:15:02.520 align:middle line:90%
>> Wow.

00:15:02.520 --> 00:15:06.020 align:middle line:84%
>> My picture of a man with
six foot three, really,

00:15:06.020 --> 00:15:08.710 align:middle line:90%
really black, muscular.

00:15:08.710 --> 00:15:11.210 align:middle line:84%
I could run into him and
he wouldn't be moved.

00:15:11.210 --> 00:15:13.630 align:middle line:90%
This was not in my picture.

00:15:13.630 --> 00:15:15.040 align:middle line:90%
This is what-- so he was--

00:15:15.040 --> 00:15:17.210 align:middle line:84%
he was a nice looking
man, a nice man.

00:15:17.210 --> 00:15:18.400 align:middle line:90%
I liked him OK.

00:15:18.400 --> 00:15:19.880 align:middle line:90%
>> But he wasn't your picture.

00:15:19.880 --> 00:15:21.970 align:middle line:84%
>> But he wasn't my
picture of a man.

00:15:21.970 --> 00:15:25.120 align:middle line:84%
So we started talking,
doing this business deal

00:15:25.120 --> 00:15:27.310 align:middle line:90%
about being the spokesperson.

00:15:27.310 --> 00:15:30.940 align:middle line:84%
I don't know where the
conversation changed.

00:15:30.940 --> 00:15:35.380 align:middle line:84%
But somewhere long distance, it
changed from this business deal

00:15:35.380 --> 00:15:37.450 align:middle line:90%
to you're a good friend.

00:15:37.450 --> 00:15:41.650 align:middle line:84%
So we became friends
on the telephone.

00:15:41.650 --> 00:15:45.860 align:middle line:84%
And then, I don't know when,
but one night, he calls me up.

00:15:45.860 --> 00:15:49.810 align:middle line:84%
And for the time,
it was 11 o'clock

00:15:49.810 --> 00:15:55.010 align:middle line:84%
in Los Angeles, which
made it 1:00 in Chicago.

00:15:55.010 --> 00:15:56.260 align:middle line:90%
And he called me.

00:15:56.260 --> 00:15:57.960 align:middle line:90%
And I'm sitting at my desk.

00:15:57.960 --> 00:15:58.960 align:middle line:90%
And I look at the clock.

00:15:58.960 --> 00:16:01.510 align:middle line:84%
And he's talked to
me for 45 minutes.

00:16:01.510 --> 00:16:04.570 align:middle line:84%
And he hasn't said
anything about no business.

00:16:04.570 --> 00:16:08.890 align:middle line:84%
So at this 45 minute
conversation on the phone,

00:16:08.890 --> 00:16:09.945 align:middle line:90%
I knew--

00:16:09.945 --> 00:16:10.820 align:middle line:90%
>> He had showed you.

00:16:10.820 --> 00:16:11.620 align:middle line:10%
>> That this was--

00:16:11.620 --> 00:16:12.910 align:middle line:10%
Franklin was the one.

00:16:12.910 --> 00:16:15.160 align:middle line:10%
Because it wasn't
rushing to fall in love.

00:16:15.160 --> 00:16:16.840 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't, "Ooh, you
look good to me."

00:16:16.840 --> 00:16:19.540 align:middle line:84%
It had grown from
business to a friendship.

00:16:19.540 --> 00:16:22.090 align:middle line:90%
He had a good mind to talk to.

00:16:22.090 --> 00:16:23.420 align:middle line:90%
He was a lot of fun.

00:16:23.420 --> 00:16:26.980 align:middle line:84%
I knew all this before the
45 minute call, you see?

00:16:26.980 --> 00:16:30.280 align:middle line:90%
So I knew that he was the one.

00:16:30.280 --> 00:16:31.480 align:middle line:90%
Repeat after me.

00:16:31.480 --> 00:16:32.440 align:middle line:10%
I am

00:16:32.440 --> 00:16:34.060 align:middle line:10%
>> I am.

00:16:34.060 --> 00:16:36.070 align:middle line:90%
>> An unconditional lover.

00:16:36.070 --> 00:16:39.090 align:middle line:90%
>> An unconditional lover.

00:16:39.090 --> 00:16:42.760 align:middle line:84%
>> That means I can
love through anything.

00:16:42.760 --> 00:16:43.660 align:middle line:90%
I love you.

00:16:43.660 --> 00:16:44.740 align:middle line:90%
>> I love you.

00:16:44.740 --> 00:16:46.080 align:middle line:90%
>> With the love of the Lord.

00:16:46.080 --> 00:16:47.470 align:middle line:90%
>> With the love of the Lord.

00:16:47.470 --> 00:16:48.760 align:middle line:90%
>> I surround you.

00:16:48.760 --> 00:16:49.620 align:middle line:90%
>> I surround you.

00:16:49.620 --> 00:16:50.420 align:middle line:90%
>> Right here.

00:16:50.420 --> 00:16:51.530 align:middle line:90%
>> Right here.

00:16:51.530 --> 00:16:52.330 align:middle line:90%
>> Right now.

00:16:52.330 --> 00:16:53.315 align:middle line:90%
>> Right now.

00:16:53.315 --> 00:16:54.190 align:middle line:90%
>> With the powerful.

00:16:54.190 --> 00:16:55.771 align:middle line:90%
>> With the powerful.

00:16:55.771 --> 00:16:56.745 align:middle line:90%
>> Unconditional love.

00:16:56.745 --> 00:16:57.719 align:middle line:90%
>> Unconditional love.

00:16:57.719 --> 00:16:59.038 align:middle line:90%
>> Of God.

00:16:59.038 --> 00:17:00.830 align:middle line:90%
>> Of God.

00:17:00.830 --> 00:17:02.247 align:middle line:84%
>> You ready for
a dicey question?

00:17:02.247 --> 00:17:03.579 align:middle line:90%
>> I don't know what that means.

00:17:03.579 --> 00:17:06.250 align:middle line:84%
But if you can stand the answer,
I can stand the question.

00:17:06.250 --> 00:17:08.530 align:middle line:10%
>> Is there anybody who
ever says to you, "Della,

00:17:08.530 --> 00:17:11.950 align:middle line:10%
that is the stupidest
idea I've ever heard."

00:17:11.950 --> 00:17:14.380 align:middle line:90%
>> I think most of the time.

00:17:14.380 --> 00:17:17.890 align:middle line:84%
Because God does not
make common sense.

00:17:17.890 --> 00:17:21.010 align:middle line:84%
There's nothing
common about God.

00:17:21.010 --> 00:17:23.980 align:middle line:84%
And when you listen
to God, He tells

00:17:23.980 --> 00:17:29.350 align:middle line:84%
you to do things that he doesn't
necessarily tell other people

00:17:29.350 --> 00:17:30.790 align:middle line:90%
that you're going to do.

00:17:30.790 --> 00:17:33.140 align:middle line:90%
It has nothing to do with them.

00:17:33.140 --> 00:17:34.670 align:middle line:90%
He speaks to me.

00:17:34.670 --> 00:17:37.660 align:middle line:84%
And from where you're
sitting, I imagine

00:17:37.660 --> 00:17:40.510 align:middle line:84%
what I'm doing does
look stupid, because you

00:17:40.510 --> 00:17:42.310 align:middle line:90%
don't have any information.

00:17:42.310 --> 00:17:44.620 align:middle line:84%
That's why you have
to have the faith

00:17:44.620 --> 00:17:47.170 align:middle line:84%
to know that you
know what you know.

00:17:47.170 --> 00:17:50.830 align:middle line:84%
For an example, as
I told you earlier,

00:17:50.830 --> 00:17:54.490 align:middle line:84%
I knew that Franklin
was what God had sent

00:17:54.490 --> 00:17:56.920 align:middle line:90%
to me, because God told me so.

00:17:56.920 --> 00:18:00.760 align:middle line:84%
But God didn't
tell Franklin, OK?

00:18:00.760 --> 00:18:01.840 align:middle line:90%
All right?

00:18:01.840 --> 00:18:03.320 align:middle line:90%
So for four years--

00:18:03.320 --> 00:18:04.820 align:middle line:90%
I'm so serious.

00:18:04.820 --> 00:18:07.990 align:middle line:84%
So for four years,
it was my faith,

00:18:07.990 --> 00:18:11.560 align:middle line:84%
knowing that this
was my stuff, that I

00:18:11.560 --> 00:18:13.930 align:middle line:84%
took some things that--
and it made me grow.

00:18:13.930 --> 00:18:15.670 align:middle line:84%
Because when I met
Franklin, I was--

00:18:15.670 --> 00:18:19.070 align:middle line:90%
I was powerful and successful.

00:18:19.070 --> 00:18:20.860 align:middle line:84%
And my attitude was,
"If you can't give me

00:18:20.860 --> 00:18:22.330 align:middle line:84%
what I want when
I want it, you can

00:18:22.330 --> 00:18:23.621 align:middle line:90%
keep it 'cause I don't need it.

00:18:23.621 --> 00:18:25.090 align:middle line:90%
I'll get it myself."

00:18:25.090 --> 00:18:28.630 align:middle line:84%
And those four years, I
don't mean they reduced me.

00:18:28.630 --> 00:18:29.980 align:middle line:90%
Don't misunderstand me.

00:18:29.980 --> 00:18:31.310 align:middle line:90%
He didn't break me down.

00:18:31.310 --> 00:18:32.660 align:middle line:90%
I'm not trying to say that.

00:18:32.660 --> 00:18:38.020 align:middle line:84%
But I learned how to work
with him, to be one with him,

00:18:38.020 --> 00:18:39.490 align:middle line:90%
to let some of my stuff go.

00:18:39.490 --> 00:18:42.160 align:middle line:84%
And he learned how to let
some of this stuff go.

00:18:42.160 --> 00:18:45.010 align:middle line:90%
And we became one, you see?

00:18:45.010 --> 00:18:48.190 align:middle line:84%
But I don't mind, you
know, what you think of.

00:18:48.190 --> 00:18:50.140 align:middle line:84%
Everything you think
is your problem.

00:18:50.140 --> 00:18:51.760 align:middle line:90%
It's not my problem.

00:18:51.760 --> 00:18:53.030 align:middle line:90%
>> So let me ask you this.

00:18:53.030 --> 00:18:53.830 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:18:53.830 --> 00:18:57.710 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you think people
ever think, "Della Reese,

00:18:57.710 --> 00:18:59.820 align:middle line:90%
she can be tough."

00:18:59.820 --> 00:19:01.530 align:middle line:90%
>> I'll say it again.

00:19:01.530 --> 00:19:03.990 align:middle line:90%
What you think is your problem.

00:19:03.990 --> 00:19:05.550 align:middle line:90%
That's not my problem.

00:19:05.550 --> 00:19:09.840 align:middle line:84%
Yes, if I need to be
tough, I can be tough.

00:19:09.840 --> 00:19:12.780 align:middle line:84%
Yes, if I need to
be sweet, I'm sugar.

00:19:12.780 --> 00:19:16.500 align:middle line:84%
Yes, if you make me mad,
you will know I'm angry.

00:19:16.500 --> 00:19:19.840 align:middle line:84%
Yes, if you appeal to
me, I want to help you.

00:19:19.840 --> 00:19:21.750 align:middle line:84%
I want to be--
yes, I'm a human--

00:19:21.750 --> 00:19:24.610 align:middle line:84%
part of me anyway
is a human being.

00:19:24.610 --> 00:19:26.790 align:middle line:84%
And so I have all
of those things

00:19:26.790 --> 00:19:28.740 align:middle line:90%
that you're asking me about.

00:19:28.740 --> 00:19:30.720 align:middle line:84%
>> I want to learn
how to do that.

00:19:30.720 --> 00:19:35.700 align:middle line:84%
I want to learn how to take
someone's opinion of me

00:19:35.700 --> 00:19:37.510 align:middle line:84%
and say, "That's
your responsibility."

00:19:37.510 --> 00:19:38.950 align:middle line:90%
>> You just did it.

00:19:38.950 --> 00:19:39.750 align:middle line:90%
>> I did?

00:19:39.750 --> 00:19:40.550 align:middle line:90%
>> You just did it.

00:19:40.550 --> 00:19:41.350 align:middle line:90%
>> Did I do it?

00:19:41.350 --> 00:19:42.420 align:middle line:90%
>> It's just that simple.

00:19:42.420 --> 00:19:42.750 align:middle line:90%
Oh.

00:19:42.750 --> 00:19:43.440 align:middle line:90%
>> You just did it.

00:19:43.440 --> 00:19:44.140 align:middle line:90%
Didn't she just do it?

00:19:44.140 --> 00:19:45.070 align:middle line:90%
Didn't you hear her just do it?

00:19:45.070 --> 00:19:45.780 align:middle line:90%
She just did it.

00:19:45.780 --> 00:19:46.650 align:middle line:90%
>> I did it, didn't I?

00:19:46.650 --> 00:19:47.120 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:19:47.120 --> 00:19:48.240 align:middle line:90%
That's all you have to do.

00:19:48.240 --> 00:19:49.350 align:middle line:90%
>> It's your responsibility.

00:19:49.350 --> 00:19:50.150 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:19:50.150 --> 00:19:52.260 align:middle line:10%
What you think-- listen,
I'm having enough trouble

00:19:52.260 --> 00:19:53.640 align:middle line:10%
working with what I'm thinking.

00:19:53.640 --> 00:19:55.890 align:middle line:10%
I don't have time to be
working with what I'm thinking

00:19:55.890 --> 00:19:57.580 align:middle line:10%
and what you're thinking, too.

00:19:57.580 --> 00:19:58.380 align:middle line:90%
You see?

00:19:58.380 --> 00:20:00.250 align:middle line:84%
You're not supposed to
be judging me anyway.

00:20:00.250 --> 00:20:02.700 align:middle line:84%
The Bible says, "Judge not
so you won't be judged."

00:20:02.700 --> 00:20:04.680 align:middle line:84%
So you think this--
see, that's what causes

00:20:04.680 --> 00:20:06.420 align:middle line:90%
the wars and the confusion.

00:20:06.420 --> 00:20:08.700 align:middle line:84%
You think what I
just did was stupid.

00:20:08.700 --> 00:20:10.440 align:middle line:84%
And I have to
retaliate and think

00:20:10.440 --> 00:20:12.030 align:middle line:90%
what you're doing is stupid.

00:20:12.030 --> 00:20:14.130 align:middle line:84%
And so now here we are
in the stupid thing

00:20:14.130 --> 00:20:15.060 align:middle line:90%
going back and forth.

00:20:15.060 --> 00:20:17.696 align:middle line:84%
Neither one of us
are progressing.

00:20:17.696 --> 00:20:19.320 align:middle line:84%
We're wasting time
here, because you're

00:20:19.320 --> 00:20:23.140 align:middle line:84%
going to do and be
and have who you are.

00:20:23.140 --> 00:20:26.420 align:middle line:84%
What you draw to you is
what you're going to have.

00:20:26.420 --> 00:20:28.290 align:middle line:84%
And if I let you draw
me into stupidity,

00:20:28.290 --> 00:20:29.730 align:middle line:90%
that's what I'm going to have.

00:20:29.730 --> 00:20:31.290 align:middle line:84%
I have to have sense
enough to say, "Well, no, I

00:20:31.290 --> 00:20:32.400 align:middle line:90%
don't need to go there.

00:20:32.400 --> 00:20:33.750 align:middle line:90%
You have that."

00:20:33.750 --> 00:20:35.250 align:middle line:90%
>> Did you always know this?

00:20:35.250 --> 00:20:36.515 align:middle line:90%
>> I think so.

00:20:36.515 --> 00:20:38.730 align:middle line:84%
But see, I didn't
always know that I

00:20:38.730 --> 00:20:40.690 align:middle line:90%
had the right to know this.

00:20:40.690 --> 00:20:41.490 align:middle line:90%
You see?

00:20:41.490 --> 00:20:45.060 align:middle line:84%
I always knew this and I always
responded to my knowledge.

00:20:45.060 --> 00:20:48.030 align:middle line:84%
But it used to bother
me if you thought

00:20:48.030 --> 00:20:50.350 align:middle line:90%
I wasn't absolutely correct.

00:20:50.350 --> 00:20:52.000 align:middle line:90%
It used to bother me if you--

00:20:52.000 --> 00:20:54.690 align:middle line:84%
ah, I couldn't care less if I
sat down like this and said,

00:20:54.690 --> 00:20:55.980 align:middle line:90%
"I'm going to care.

00:20:55.980 --> 00:20:57.210 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to care.

00:20:57.210 --> 00:20:58.900 align:middle line:84%
I'm just going to sit
here 'til I care."

00:20:58.900 --> 00:21:00.150 align:middle line:90%
I would probably have a beard.

00:21:00.150 --> 00:21:04.650 align:middle line:90%


00:21:04.650 --> 00:21:08.730 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the reasons that
I have personally loved you

00:21:08.730 --> 00:21:13.110 align:middle line:84%
for as long as I've known you
and the reason so many do is

00:21:13.110 --> 00:21:15.640 align:middle line:90%
that you, Della, have a--

00:21:15.640 --> 00:21:17.850 align:middle line:90%
it's a presence of joy.

00:21:17.850 --> 00:21:21.360 align:middle line:84%
You walk into a room and
you can feel your joy,

00:21:21.360 --> 00:21:25.140 align:middle line:84%
though you have been through
trials and tribulations.

00:21:25.140 --> 00:21:28.500 align:middle line:84%
Other people have been through
trials and tribulations

00:21:28.500 --> 00:21:32.100 align:middle line:84%
and they have not walked into
the light and they are angry.

00:21:32.100 --> 00:21:34.240 align:middle line:90%
You walked into the light.

00:21:34.240 --> 00:21:35.990 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, no, I was in the light.

00:21:35.990 --> 00:21:36.285 align:middle line:90%
>> Always?

00:21:36.285 --> 00:21:37.500 align:middle line:90%
>> You see, I'm telling you--

00:21:37.500 --> 00:21:39.090 align:middle line:90%
I just told you about my momma.

00:21:39.090 --> 00:21:40.830 align:middle line:90%
>> Tell me again so I know.

00:21:40.830 --> 00:21:42.420 align:middle line:84%
>> For as long as
I could remember,

00:21:42.420 --> 00:21:47.610 align:middle line:84%
I have been consciously
aware of God,

00:21:47.610 --> 00:21:49.590 align:middle line:90%
of the Christ inside of me.

00:21:49.590 --> 00:21:52.540 align:middle line:84%
So I've always
been in the light.

00:21:52.540 --> 00:21:56.970 align:middle line:84%
And once, once he brings you
through something-- oh Father,

00:21:56.970 --> 00:21:58.470 align:middle line:90%
please let me get this over--

00:21:58.470 --> 00:22:03.480 align:middle line:84%
once you know that you're
in the direst of places

00:22:03.480 --> 00:22:07.290 align:middle line:84%
and you speak to Him and
He brings you through,

00:22:07.290 --> 00:22:09.720 align:middle line:90%
you can never be captured again.

00:22:09.720 --> 00:22:11.790 align:middle line:84%
Because you know that
all you have to do

00:22:11.790 --> 00:22:15.120 align:middle line:84%
is go to Him and speak
to him and that he

00:22:15.120 --> 00:22:18.660 align:middle line:84%
is, through your faith, going
to bring you out of this.

00:22:18.660 --> 00:22:21.210 align:middle line:90%
There's nothing but joy in that.

00:22:21.210 --> 00:22:23.910 align:middle line:84%
It's when you are
confused, and you

00:22:23.910 --> 00:22:25.830 align:middle line:84%
don't know what
you're going to do,

00:22:25.830 --> 00:22:29.550 align:middle line:84%
and you don't know how it's
going to come out that you feel

00:22:29.550 --> 00:22:31.380 align:middle line:90%
you are part of the darkness.

00:22:31.380 --> 00:22:33.720 align:middle line:84%
That's what negativity
does to you.

00:22:33.720 --> 00:22:38.400 align:middle line:84%
It confuses you so that it
makes you separate yourself

00:22:38.400 --> 00:22:41.840 align:middle line:84%
from your power, which is
the God that's inside of you.

00:22:41.840 --> 00:22:43.180 align:middle line:90%
That's his whole point.

00:22:43.180 --> 00:22:45.677 align:middle line:90%
I won't let Him do that to me.

00:22:45.677 --> 00:22:47.010 align:middle line:90%
>> God has answered your prayer.

00:22:47.010 --> 00:22:48.250 align:middle line:90%
Because you know what?

00:22:48.250 --> 00:22:49.050 align:middle line:90%
I got it.

00:22:49.050 --> 00:22:49.922 align:middle line:90%
>> Good.

00:22:49.922 --> 00:22:53.778 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:22:53.778 --> 00:22:58.610 align:middle line:90%


00:22:58.610 --> 00:23:02.630 align:middle line:10%
When you love your enemies,
you strip them of power.

00:23:02.630 --> 00:23:07.280 align:middle line:10%
When you hate them, you
give them your power.

00:23:07.280 --> 00:23:10.460 align:middle line:84%
Because what you have your
mind on has its mind on you.

00:23:10.460 --> 00:23:11.960 align:middle line:84%
In order to hate
somebody, you've

00:23:11.960 --> 00:23:13.501 align:middle line:84%
got to think about
them all the time.

00:23:13.501 --> 00:23:16.440 align:middle line:90%


00:23:16.440 --> 00:23:20.330 align:middle line:84%
>> Della persevered in the face
of racial discrimination by her

00:23:20.330 --> 00:23:26.190 align:middle line:84%
will, her determination, but
most importantly her faith.

00:23:26.190 --> 00:23:30.440 align:middle line:10%
>> What brought
me from the slums,

00:23:30.440 --> 00:23:34.850 align:middle line:10%
which was before the ghetto,
to where I am now was the fact

00:23:34.850 --> 00:23:39.140 align:middle line:10%
that I sincerely believed that
God wanted for me the very

00:23:39.140 --> 00:23:41.750 align:middle line:10%
best, that he had
given me this talent.

00:23:41.750 --> 00:23:45.440 align:middle line:10%
And all I had to do was go
and He would go with me.

00:23:45.440 --> 00:23:48.740 align:middle line:84%
And if I would open my
mouth, He would speak for me,

00:23:48.740 --> 00:23:51.230 align:middle line:84%
that He would never
leave me nor forsake me.

00:23:51.230 --> 00:23:54.230 align:middle line:84%
My mother showed
me that every day.

00:23:54.230 --> 00:23:55.800 align:middle line:90%
I took that with me.

00:23:55.800 --> 00:24:01.130 align:middle line:84%
So when I got knocked down, I
bounced up and I started again.

00:24:01.130 --> 00:24:03.446 align:middle line:90%
Bless people who curse you.

00:24:03.446 --> 00:24:05.320 align:middle line:84%
Jesus hanging on the
cross blessed them folks

00:24:05.320 --> 00:24:06.694 align:middle line:84%
saying, "Forgive
them, Lord, they

00:24:06.694 --> 00:24:08.510 align:middle line:90%
don't know what they're doing."

00:24:08.510 --> 00:24:11.677 align:middle line:90%
That's your statement.

00:24:11.677 --> 00:24:14.010 align:middle line:84%
I forgive you, because you
don't know what you're doing.

00:24:14.010 --> 00:24:17.960 align:middle line:84%
You don't know who mess
with a child of God.

00:24:17.960 --> 00:24:20.490 align:middle line:84%
And you don't know I'm
holding my zapping power back.

00:24:20.490 --> 00:24:26.478 align:middle line:90%


00:24:26.478 --> 00:24:28.150 align:middle line:84%
You don't know
what you're doing.

00:24:28.150 --> 00:24:32.070 align:middle line:84%
I'm just going to forgive
you and let you slide.

00:24:32.070 --> 00:24:33.460 align:middle line:90%
I'm a creative individual.

00:24:33.460 --> 00:24:36.400 align:middle line:84%
I must be about
creating something.

00:24:36.400 --> 00:24:39.700 align:middle line:84%
So I don't know about
living on the edge.

00:24:39.700 --> 00:24:40.900 align:middle line:90%
Every day is exciting.

00:24:40.900 --> 00:24:42.410 align:middle line:90%
I wake up.

00:24:42.410 --> 00:24:45.200 align:middle line:84%
I woke up this
morning by myself.

00:24:45.200 --> 00:24:47.640 align:middle line:90%
I got up out of bed by myself.

00:24:47.640 --> 00:24:50.110 align:middle line:84%
I washed my face and
brushed my teeth by my--

00:24:50.110 --> 00:24:52.800 align:middle line:84%
I walked down them
steps by myself.

00:24:52.800 --> 00:24:54.170 align:middle line:90%
I got dressed by myself.

00:24:54.170 --> 00:24:55.730 align:middle line:90%
There was no nurse.

00:24:55.730 --> 00:24:58.380 align:middle line:90%
There was no doctor.

00:24:58.380 --> 00:25:00.510 align:middle line:90%
There were no x-rays.

00:25:00.510 --> 00:25:01.470 align:middle line:90%
There were no shots.

00:25:01.470 --> 00:25:03.180 align:middle line:90%
There were no pills.

00:25:03.180 --> 00:25:04.509 align:middle line:90%
I got up by the grace of God.

00:25:04.509 --> 00:25:05.550 align:middle line:90%
And that day is exciting.

00:25:05.550 --> 00:25:06.400 align:middle line:90%
It's already exciting.

00:25:06.400 --> 00:25:08.460 align:middle line:84%
It's like, "I can get back
into bed, because I've

00:25:08.460 --> 00:25:10.200 align:middle line:90%
had a good day already."

00:25:10.200 --> 00:25:11.790 align:middle line:90%
That's just my nature.

00:25:11.790 --> 00:25:14.220 align:middle line:84%
>> Which leads me to something
else I was thinking about.

00:25:14.220 --> 00:25:18.790 align:middle line:10%
When I think of your
schedule, I couldn't do it.

00:25:18.790 --> 00:25:23.156 align:middle line:10%
I know men who couldn't
do your schedule.

00:25:23.156 --> 00:25:24.780 align:middle line:84%
>> Is that supposed
to be a compliment?

00:25:24.780 --> 00:25:25.910 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh yes, ma'am.

00:25:25.910 --> 00:25:26.710 align:middle line:90%
>> Why?

00:25:26.710 --> 00:25:27.510 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:25:27.510 --> 00:25:29.550 align:middle line:84%
Because a man couldn't
do it and I could do it?

00:25:29.550 --> 00:25:30.841 align:middle line:90%
Why could that be a compliment?

00:25:30.841 --> 00:25:32.120 align:middle line:90%
That's another whole show.

00:25:32.120 --> 00:25:32.920 align:middle line:90%
Let's go on.

00:25:32.920 --> 00:25:34.086 align:middle line:90%
>> Well no, let's stay here.

00:25:34.086 --> 00:25:35.790 align:middle line:90%
Let's stay here.

00:25:35.790 --> 00:25:36.660 align:middle line:90%
You know why?

00:25:36.660 --> 00:25:38.040 align:middle line:90%
The physicality of it.

00:25:38.040 --> 00:25:39.600 align:middle line:90%
>> No, it's not.

00:25:39.600 --> 00:25:41.610 align:middle line:90%
I have a piece of God in me.

00:25:41.610 --> 00:25:43.740 align:middle line:84%
The piece of God in
me is the same size

00:25:43.740 --> 00:25:46.050 align:middle line:84%
as the piece of God in
every man in this room.

00:25:46.050 --> 00:25:49.920 align:middle line:84%
Nobody has any more god
in them than I have in me.

00:25:49.920 --> 00:25:53.910 align:middle line:84%
And if I-- if I call on the God
in me, all that God is I am.

00:25:53.910 --> 00:25:55.650 align:middle line:90%
All that He has is mine.

00:25:55.650 --> 00:25:58.060 align:middle line:84%
If I call on that,
I can do anything,

00:25:58.060 --> 00:26:01.080 align:middle line:90%
be I male, female, whatever.

00:26:01.080 --> 00:26:05.220 align:middle line:84%
>> Are there ever mornings,
particularly Sunday mornings

00:26:05.220 --> 00:26:10.324 align:middle line:84%
when you preach, that you
open your eyes and you say,

00:26:10.324 --> 00:26:12.339 align:middle line:90%
"I don't want to do this?"

00:26:12.339 --> 00:26:14.880 align:middle line:84%
>> Oh, there are mornings when
I say that but not necessarily

00:26:14.880 --> 00:26:15.900 align:middle line:90%
Sunday mornings.

00:26:15.900 --> 00:26:18.730 align:middle line:84%
Because Sunday morning is
when I get revitalized.

00:26:18.730 --> 00:26:21.370 align:middle line:84%
That may be the only morning
that I want to get up.

00:26:21.370 --> 00:26:24.040 align:middle line:84%
But this morning, I didn't want
to get up and come here and be

00:26:24.040 --> 00:26:24.840 align:middle line:90%
with you.

00:26:24.840 --> 00:26:27.180 align:middle line:84%
I just wanted to lay there
and just get way down there

00:26:27.180 --> 00:26:30.570 align:middle line:84%
and turn that electric blanket
on, just get way down in there.

00:26:30.570 --> 00:26:31.800 align:middle line:90%
That's what I wanted.

00:26:31.800 --> 00:26:35.400 align:middle line:84%
But not on a Sunday morning,
because on Sunday morning, I

00:26:35.400 --> 00:26:38.070 align:middle line:84%
get to be with
people of like mind.

00:26:38.070 --> 00:26:40.380 align:middle line:84%
And we get to experience
the spirit of God.

00:26:40.380 --> 00:26:43.320 align:middle line:84%
So Sunday, for me, is
the best day of the week.

00:26:43.320 --> 00:26:44.970 align:middle line:84%
But there are many
mornings I don't

00:26:44.970 --> 00:26:47.610 align:middle line:90%
want to be picked up at 5:30.

00:26:47.610 --> 00:26:52.490 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to be picked up at
6:30 a lot of those mornings.

00:26:52.490 --> 00:26:54.300 align:middle line:90%
>> What gets you out of bed?

00:26:54.300 --> 00:26:58.080 align:middle line:84%
>> I took the job to do
"Touched by an Angel."

00:26:58.080 --> 00:27:00.150 align:middle line:90%
I signed a contract.

00:27:00.150 --> 00:27:04.850 align:middle line:90%
I had the opportunity to say no.

00:27:04.850 --> 00:27:07.430 align:middle line:84%
So when I signed the
contract, I took on--

00:27:07.430 --> 00:27:10.460 align:middle line:84%
I agreed to "Pick
me up at 5:30."

00:27:10.460 --> 00:27:12.890 align:middle line:84%
I agreed to "Pick
me up at 6:30."

00:27:12.890 --> 00:27:16.240 align:middle line:84%
I agreed to "I will stay here
and work until you get it."

00:27:16.240 --> 00:27:17.480 align:middle line:90%
Now see, that because--

00:27:17.480 --> 00:27:20.400 align:middle line:84%
if I had said no, I could've
laid in bed all day every day.

00:27:20.400 --> 00:27:21.200 align:middle line:90%
You see?

00:27:21.200 --> 00:27:24.230 align:middle line:84%
But I said yes and
I signed my name.

00:27:24.230 --> 00:27:26.780 align:middle line:84%
So that-- you know, you grumble
a little bit, but you get up

00:27:26.780 --> 00:27:27.860 align:middle line:90%
and you do what you have to do.

00:27:27.860 --> 00:27:30.359 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, it's fascinating
that you say Sunday is the one

00:27:30.359 --> 00:27:32.360 align:middle line:90%
day that you do get up.

00:27:32.360 --> 00:27:33.899 align:middle line:84%
Because I would
think, boy, that's

00:27:33.899 --> 00:27:35.690 align:middle line:84%
the day that you're
most tired and you feel

00:27:35.690 --> 00:27:37.310 align:middle line:90%
most entitled to stay in bed.

00:27:37.310 --> 00:27:40.260 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, no, no, no.

00:27:40.260 --> 00:27:43.950 align:middle line:84%
>> I think that when you are
given the gift of being able

00:27:43.950 --> 00:27:49.950 align:middle line:84%
to, say, sing like you do, one
of the things you have to do is

00:27:49.950 --> 00:27:53.310 align:middle line:84%
acknowledge that God gave it to
you and own the gift and say,

00:27:53.310 --> 00:27:54.270 align:middle line:90%
"I can do it."

00:27:54.270 --> 00:27:56.900 align:middle line:90%
And that makes you better at it.

00:27:56.900 --> 00:28:01.300 align:middle line:84%
Is it the same thing
when you are a minister

00:28:01.300 --> 00:28:02.860 align:middle line:90%
and you preach the way you do?

00:28:02.860 --> 00:28:05.440 align:middle line:90%
Because I have seen you preach.

00:28:05.440 --> 00:28:08.500 align:middle line:84%
Is that something you have to
own and say, "That's a gift

00:28:08.500 --> 00:28:09.670 align:middle line:90%
and I'm good at it?"

00:28:09.670 --> 00:28:10.840 align:middle line:90%
>> It is.

00:28:10.840 --> 00:28:14.880 align:middle line:84%
The criteria for
me as a minister

00:28:14.880 --> 00:28:20.600 align:middle line:84%
is of myself, of myself,
I can do nothing.

00:28:20.600 --> 00:28:25.440 align:middle line:84%
Because as an
entertainer, it is myself.

00:28:25.440 --> 00:28:28.880 align:middle line:90%
I depend on myself to do it.

00:28:28.880 --> 00:28:30.890 align:middle line:90%
I depend on my voice.

00:28:30.890 --> 00:28:33.200 align:middle line:90%
I depend on my stage knowledge.

00:28:33.200 --> 00:28:35.390 align:middle line:90%
I depend on the arrangement.

00:28:35.390 --> 00:28:37.640 align:middle line:90%
I depend on the musicians.

00:28:37.640 --> 00:28:42.650 align:middle line:84%
I come from the God in me, but
I am in charge of these things,

00:28:42.650 --> 00:28:47.150 align:middle line:84%
because this is the talent
He gave me to work with.

00:28:47.150 --> 00:28:51.950 align:middle line:84%
As a minister, I claim the
right to teach the lesson

00:28:51.950 --> 00:28:54.740 align:middle line:90%
as Jesus would have taught it.

00:28:54.740 --> 00:28:59.570 align:middle line:84%
And Jesus's criterion is "Of
myself, I can do nothing.

00:28:59.570 --> 00:29:01.400 align:middle line:90%
Get me out of the way.

00:29:01.400 --> 00:29:04.010 align:middle line:84%
Come up through me
and say the things

00:29:04.010 --> 00:29:06.230 align:middle line:90%
that these people need to hear."

00:29:06.230 --> 00:29:09.679 align:middle line:84%
The people who come to the
church, I don't know them.

00:29:09.679 --> 00:29:11.720 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I haven't been in
touch with them every--

00:29:11.720 --> 00:29:13.460 align:middle line:90%
I don't know what they need.

00:29:13.460 --> 00:29:15.930 align:middle line:90%
Only God knows what they need.

00:29:15.930 --> 00:29:18.566 align:middle line:84%
So that's one of the times
when people say-- especially

00:29:18.566 --> 00:29:19.940 align:middle line:84%
the people in the
church who have

